{"build_type":"tool","description":"Install and enable a systemd USER unit in one call, fully automatic, through the stock CLIs (mkdir, ln, systemctl) via the capture primitive. Request fields (all paths as data): mkdir, ln, systemctl (binary paths), unit (unit name to enable), user_dir (systemd user unit directory to create), current_target (what the CAS current pointer points to, e.g. the unit filename), current_link (the CAS current pointer path to create), user_link (the systemd user path symlink to create pointing at the CAS current). Steps: mkdir -p user_dir; ln -sfn current_target current_link; ln -sfn current_link user_link; systemctl --user daemon-reload; systemctl --user enable unit. XDG_RUNTIME_DIR is auto-derived. Emits {unit, ok, output} where output is the enable result and ok is 1 when enable exited zero. Does NOT start the unit (avoids racing a running instance on the same port).","module_name":"install-systemd-account-service-activating-through-symlinks","package_name":"install-systemd-account-service-activating-through-symlinks","function_definitions":{"install-systemd-account-service-activating-through-symlinks":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"__st_se","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"error"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"__st_sm","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"message"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"__st_ve","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"tool-broken"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"__st_vm","variable_type"